  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LRC ICT support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Beirut, Lebanon</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve LRC&#x2019;s ICT compliance with Data Protection and Data Responsibility Movement Standards. The main objective is to improve the governance and management of the ICT systems and to embed an information security culture which aims to protect the data of the people LRC serves, and prevent doing harm to these people by the use of data and information systems while relying on standards and well-known best practices.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In its quest to strengthen its information, digital, and cybersecurity strategy, the Lebanese Red Cross took a strategic decision to assess its information security risks, update its ICT strategy, define a roadmap to implement an Information Security Management System (ISMS) and ultimately get ISO certified. Getting the ISO certification would allow LRC to become compliant with GDPR standards, as well as enhance data sharing agreements and ensure that the data sharing processes safeguard the information shared by having the proper policies and procedures in place.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanese Red Cross Society and its beneficiaries</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to revise the ICT Unit&#x2019;s strategy for the upcoming 5 years in order to improve its alignment with digital transformation and to be able to efficiently use LRC&#x2019;s existing resources.</narrative>
  </description>
